For [G]your childish love and vows lasted [C]only one short [G]year
Now you’ve gone away to [C]be an[D7]other's [G]bride
You will [C]never know the [G]pain
That I felt the day you left
[C]Should you ever wed [G]again
[D7]Let me wish you love and [G]wealth
While that same old whippoorwill breaks the [C]silence on the [G]hill
I stand and gaze upon the faded [D7]wall
[G]Where your picture used to hang in a [C]little golden [G]frame
And a vision of your [C]smile [D7]I still [G]recall
Repeat #2
